overview: The user initiated a request to significantly improve the aesthetics
  of their sleep questionnaire application, which they felt was too generic. The
  assistant conducted a detailed analysis of the existing design, identifying
  shortcomings in the color palette, typography, layout, and form elements. A
  new, calming sleep-themed color palette was introduced, utilizing deep
  indigos, purples, and teal accents. Key UI components like checkboxes, radio
  buttons, sliders, and progress bars were enhanced with improved visual
  feedback and modern styling. The main questionnaire form and all individual
  sections, including the intro and report, were updated to reflect a cohesive
  and professional sleep-health aesthetic, replacing bland gray boxes with
  refined card-style groupings and themed backgrounds. Additionally, a console
  error related to  values being passed to input components was identified
  and resolved, ensuring the application's stability. The changes were
  meticulously applied and committed in logical, atomic steps, resulting in a
  polished and visually appealing user experience.
